          <!-- relationship -->
          <div class="px-2 m-2 text-3xl font-bold underline" style="width: 96%;">Relationship Addiction</div>
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row border-solid border-2 rounded-md shadow-lg p-4 m-4" style="width: 96%;">
            <div class="w-full lg:mt-0 md:w-2/5">
              <img src="images/relation.jpg" alt="relationship" class="w-full h-full max-w-md mx-auto">
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 md:w-3/5 text-justify text-lg break-words">
              <p>
                Overwhelming reliance on romantic relationships for emotional fulfillment and a sense of self-worth is
                referred to as
                relationship addiction, also known as love addiction or codependency. People battling relationship
                addiction frequently
                have a severe fear of abandonment, a tendency to get into codependent or unhealthy relationships, and
                difficulty
                establishing healthy boundaries. They might put their partner's demands above their own, disregard their
                health, and
                struggle to function independently. A loop of destructive relationships, mental distress, and a lack of
                self-identity
                can result from relationship addiction. To break free from relationship addiction and promote personal
                growth, it is
                crucial to identify and treat the root causes, look for therapy or support groups, and learn how to
                nurture self-love
                and healthy connections.
              </p>
              <p><span class="font-bold underline">Fact:</span> In 2011, over 10% of murders in the United States were
                committed by the victim's lover. When relationships come to an unwanted end, we feel pain, grief, and
                loss. <a
                  href="http://www.fbi.gov/about-us/cjis/ucr/crime-in-the-u.s/2011/crime-in-the-u.s.-2011/tables/expanded-homicide-data-table-10"
                  target="_blank" class="underline text-[#0000EE]"> (Source)</a></p>
